# Reverse proxy in front of the app container.
#
# /vnc-ws* is proxied to websockify; everything else to Flask. `handle` blocks
# give deterministic, mutually-exclusive routing (Caddy otherwise auto-orders
# directives by type, which can misroute the websocket).
#
# Note: the VNC websocket is NOT gated here. Caddy's forward_auth breaks the
# WebSocket upgrade, so the gate lives on the VNC layer instead — x11vnc
# requires a password (generated in deploy/start.sh) and the auth-gated app
# hands it to noVNC. An unauthenticated hit on /vnc-ws reaches websockify but
# can't pass VNC auth.
#
# Replace localhost with the app/websockify hosts for your topology. With the
# Cloudflare-Tunnel container setup these become the container names
# (e.g. dld:8080 / dld:6080) and Cloudflare terminates TLS; for a direct
# public deployment use the real hostname here so Caddy provisions TLS.
:80 {
	handle /vnc-ws* {
		reverse_proxy localhost:6080
	}
	handle {
		reverse_proxy localhost:8080
	}
}
